<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="214" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1977,2038]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,536]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="214" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1977,2002]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head and dorsum black; hind wings absent. Tip of head dark brown, or (in palest form) head entirely ferruginous, with median line of notum brown; metathorax and hind coxae orange, abdomen and hind legs dark brown. Tegmina broadly rounded at tip, usually boldly marked with orange on apical quarter of tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1409,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[288,1301,621,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[284,1304,607,1888]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 33. Lateral aspect of the nominate subgenus of Orthorapha (A – E) and subgenus Balsania (F – L). A – B, color varieties of O. laeta Jacobi; C, O. cassidioides Westwood, male; D, same, female; E, O. invidia sp. nov.; F, O. inflata sp. nov.; G, O. concinna (Stål); H, O. geminata (Jacobi); J, O. sagittata sp. nov.; K, O. reducta Walker; L, O. testacea Walker. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217120/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number box="[1380,1409,152,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
B) and sometimes with an orange band also across basal third, as in 
<typeStatus box="[892,990,188,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[1007,1089,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[288,1301,621,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[284,1304,607,1888]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 33. Lateral aspect of the nominate subgenus of Orthorapha (A – E) and subgenus Balsania (F – L). A – B, color varieties of O. laeta Jacobi; C, O. cassidioides Westwood, male; D, same, female; E, O. invidia sp. nov.; F, O. inflata sp. nov.; G, O. concinna (Stål); H, O. geminata (Jacobi); J, O. sagittata sp. nov.; K, O. reducta Walker; L, O. testacea Walker. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217120/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number box="[1060,1089,188,212]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Theca lamellate, sinuate in lateral aspect, apical half straight, slender, weakly tapered to rounded tip (
<figureCitation box="[989,1057,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 17" captionStartId="5.[151,264,918,941]" captionTargetBox="[217,1363,209,878]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,195,894]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 17. Male theca of Orthorapha s. s. (3 – 5), subgenus Balsania (6 – 7) and Lepyronoxia (8 – 17), lateral (A) and caudal aspect of tip (B): 3, O. cassidioides; 4, O. laeta; 5, O. invidia; 6, O. reducta; 7, O. sagittata; 8, O. obscurata; 9, O. inscripta; 10, O. decorata; 11, O. oculata; 12, O. bufo; 13, O. rana (type of O. glabrata); 14, O. subfasciata; 15, O. frontalis; 16, O. quadrimaculata; 17, O. sphaerata. Scale line: 0.05 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217116/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number box="[1042,1057,224,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Length: male 
<quantity box="[1258,1347,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
, female 
<number box="[151,185,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" value="5.7">5.7</number>
–6.0 mm. Width across pronotum: 
<quantity box="[576,714,260,284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.4" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
