<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">Remarks.</emphasis>
The orange-and-black pattern is variable (
<figureCitation box="[795,876,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[288,1301,621,1877]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[284,1304,607,1888]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 33. Lateral aspect of the nominate subgenus of Orthorapha (A – E) and subgenus Balsania (F – L). A – B, color varieties of O. laeta Jacobi; C, O. cassidioides Westwood, male; D, same, female; E, O. invidia sp. nov.; F, O. inflata sp. nov.; G, O. concinna (Stål); H, O. geminata (Jacobi); J, O. sagittata sp. nov.; K, O. reducta Walker; L, O. testacea Walker. Scale line: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/217120/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">
Fig. 
<number box="[848,876,476,500]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B) in three short series. The small size (
<quantity box="[1361,1428,476,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="214" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
) and entirely black wings associate the male 
<typeStatus box="[643,741,511,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[778,839,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="214">nigra</emphasis>
with the dark variety of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
